The man arrested in connection with arguably the country’s most devastating fire will apply for bail when next he appears in court on the 11th of January. Ayesha Ismail reports. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - The man arrested in connection with arguably the country’s most devastating fire will apply for bail when next he appears in court on the 11th of January. Parliament has been gutted, with damage estimated to run into millions of rands. But there are so still many questions. Among them is the breach of security, and even if the right man has been arrested. Watch today's court proceedings below